# App Router conventions

- A folder with `page.tsx` under `src/app/` becomes a URL. `(group)` folders don't appear in the URL;
  `[slug]` is a dynamic route; `_private` folders are NOT routed (use them to hide WIP).
- **Trailing slashes are on** — internal `<Link href>` and any URL must end in `/` (e.g. `/glossary/foo/`).
- A page sets SEO via `export const metadata = Meta(seo)` with `seo` from `src/data/<page>/seo.ts`
  (`import Meta from "@/components/Meta/Meta"`). For dynamic routes, type `generateMetadata`/`generateStaticParams`.
- **Next 16:** `params`/`searchParams` are async — `const { slug } = await params`.
- **Pages don't receive `children`** (only layouts do). A `page.tsx` that renders nothing should
  `return null`, not destructure `children`.
- **Dev-only pages:** name the file `page.dev.tsx` — it routes in `next dev` but is excluded from the
  production build (see `pageExtensions` in `next.config.js`). Example: `/dev`.
- **API routes:** `route.ts` with typed `NextRequest`/`NextResponse` from `next/server`.
- New page = (1) folder + `page.tsx`, (2) section components under `src/components/NewPages/<Page>/`,
  (3) copy + SEO in `src/data/<page>/`.
